meths_TEMethodMachine: Thermo Fisher Scientific X Series II quadrupole inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometer
meths_methodNotes: Subsampled the axis of maximum growth using a micromill with a 3 mm drill bit, at 7–8 samples per year or better than bimonthly resolution. Analytical precision reported for JCp-1.
cdata_chronologyNotes: Growth bands and luminescence established first order chronology and tuned using SrCa & LiMg matched to maxima and minima SSTs.
calib_notes: Individual coral calibration. Additional universal multi-trace element calibration calculated based on composite coral records.

meths_TEMethodMachine: Varian 820-MS quadruple ICP-MS equipped with an ArF excimer laser (193 nm) ablation system
meths_methodNotes: Ablation using a rectangualr sample area with a 40×400 μm resolution at a speed of 40um/s. NIST 614 and in-house pressed coral standards. SEM diagenesis check by A. Arzey on alternate slice of PET12.
cdata_chronologyNotes: New age model created by A. Arzey for archiving. Data from Ellis et al. 2019 was further smoothed with a 10-point bin and SrCa maxima (minima) was matched to weekly averaged Reyn_SmithOIv2 SST minima (maxima). Ellis et al. 2019 matched SrCa maxima to SST (OISST v2) minima in August and interpolated for the period summer 1990 to summer 2012 and was cross-checked using growth bands and luminescence.
meths_coralExtensionRateNotes: Max 17.27 mm/year; min 7.87 mm/year; average 12.34 mm/year. Extension rate calculated between density troughs for alternate slice of PET12 by A. Arzey.

dating_notes: 5.790 ± 0.031 ka reported 2003-09 for top of NEL01D and 6.089 ± 0.040 ka reported 2003-09 for bottom of NEL01D. cdata_coralNotes: GK2 record combines archived Saha et al. 2021, Saha et al. 2019 and Saha et al. 2018a data. BaCa & YCa values are identical (accounting for rounding) between datasets but SrCa record differs. The more recently published Saha et al. 2021 SrCa record was used for the SrCa record. REEs measured.
meths_primaryVariablesList: BaCa; Ce; Dy; Eu; Gd; Ho; La; Lu; MgCa; MnCa; Nd; Pr; Sm; SrCa; Tb; Tm; UCa; VCa; Y; Yb; YCa
meths_TEMethodMachine: Thermo X Series II Inductively Coupled Plasma-Mass Spectrometer
meths_methodNotes: Manually collected using a drill with a 2 mm diameter bit at 1mm increments, to collect a minimum of 12 sequential samples per annual band. JCp-1 & analytical precision from Saha et al. 2021. See Saha et al 2021 supplementary for all analytical precision results. Complete machine details as per Saha et al. 2019 & 2021 is Thermo X-series II ICP-MS with a CETAC - 500 auto-sampler, electron spray PC3 Peltier cooled cyclonic spray chamber and SC-FAST injection loop.
cdata_chronologyNotes: Growth bands & refined with SrCa maxima & minima matched to HadISST minima & maxima.
calib_notes: No calibration equations

meths_TEMethodMachine: A 193 nm ArF Helex MkII excimer laser system attached to a Varian 820 single collector ICPMS & Thermo iCAP RQ ICPMS
meths_methodNotes: 100 μm by and 500 μm wide, 5 Hz laser repetition rate and a scan speed of 100 μm/s. After data averaging, each point is approx. 0.59mm of coral extension. NIST 614 & NIST 612 glass standards used for Li and in-house Davies reef coral standard used for B, Mg, Ca, Sr & U.
cdata_chronologyNotes: UCa minima & maxima matched with adjusted OISST SST maxima & minima. Used SrCa, BCa, MgCa & LiMg when UCa anomalies were evident.
calib_notes: Has LiMg & BMg calibrations. Has UMTECS calibration equation(s) with different derivation compared to D'Olivo et al. 2018.
